### Problem Statement

# WHAT 

When defining the `structuredOutput` object onto the `agent.generate` options we can define the following properties : 

```ts
export type StructuredOutputOptionsBase<OUTPUT = {}> = {
  /** Model to use for the internal structuring agent. If not provided, falls back to the agent's model */
  model?: MastraModelConfig;
  /**
   * Custom instructions for the structuring agent.
   * If not provided, will generate instructions based on the schema.
   */
  instructions?: string;

  /**
   * Whether to use system prompt injection instead of native response format to coerce the LLM to respond with json text if the LLM does not natively support structured outputs.
   */
  jsonPromptInjection?: boolean;

  /**
   * Optional logger instance for structured logging
   */
  logger?: IMastraLogger;

  /**
   * Provider-specific options passed to the internal structuring agent.
   * Use this to control model behavior like reasoning effort for thinking models.
   *
   * @example
   * ```ts
   * providerOptions: {
   *   openai: { reasoningEffort: 'low' }
   * }
   * ```
   */
  providerOptions?: ProviderOptions;
} & FallbackFields<OUTPUT>;
```
however the optional `instruction` property is only relevant when defining the model property in which case it will be passed down to the custom `structured-output` processor agent. We could use a discriminated union type in order to enforce this logic

### Proposed Solution

# DISCRIMINATED UNION TYPE : 

We could express the logic above using a discriminated union type to expose the behavior to the end user. 
Something similar to the following : 

```ts
/** Fields available in both direct and processor modes */
type StructuredOutputCommonFields = {
  /**
   * Whether to use system prompt injection instead of native response format to coerce the LLM to respond with json text if the LLM does not natively support structured outputs.
   */
  jsonPromptInjection?: boolean;
};

/**
 * Fields only available when `model` is provided (processor mode).
 * In this mode, a separate structuring agent converts the main agent's
 * unstructured output into JSON using a second LLM call.
 */
type StructuredOutputProcessorFields<MODEL, OUTPUT = {}> = {
  /** Model to use for the internal structuring agent. When provided, enables two-stage processing where the main agent generates text and a separate structuring agent converts it to JSON. */
  model: MODEL;
  /**
   * Custom instructions for the structuring agent.
   * If not provided, will generate instructions based on the schema.
   */
  instructions?: string;
  /**
   * Optional logger instance for structured logging
   */
  logger?: IMastraLogger;
  /**
   * Provider-specific options passed to the internal structuring agent.
   * Use this to control model behavior like reasoning effort for thinking models.
   *
   * @example
   * ```ts
   * providerOptions: {
   *   openai: { reasoningEffort: 'low' }
   * }
   * ```
   */
  providerOptions?: ProviderOptions;
} & FallbackFields<OUTPUT>;

/**
 * When no model is provided, the agent's own LLM generates structured JSON
 * directly via native response format. Processor-only fields are not allowed.
 */
type StructuredOutputDirectFields = {
  model?: never;
  instructions?: never;
  logger?: never;
  providerOptions?: never;
  errorStrategy?: never;
  fallbackValue?: never;
};

export type StructuredOutputOptionsBase<OUTPUT = {}> = StructuredOutputCommonFields &
  (StructuredOutputProcessorFields<MastraModelConfig, OUTPUT> | StructuredOutputDirectFields);

export type StructuredOutputOptions<OUTPUT = {}> = StructuredOutputOptionsBase<OUTPUT> & {
  /** Zod schema to validate the output against */
  schema: StandardSchemaWithJSON<OUTPUT>;
};

export type PublicStructuredOutputOptions<OUTPUT = {}> = StructuredOutputOptionsBase<OUTPUT> & {
  schema: PublicSchema<OUTPUT>;
};

export type SerializableStructuredOutputOptions<OUTPUT = {}> = StructuredOutputCommonFields &
  (StructuredOutputProcessorFields<ModelRouterModelId | OpenAICompatibleConfig, OUTPUT> | StructuredOutputDirectFields) & {
  /** JSON Schema to validate the output against */
  schema: JSONSchema7;
};
```

