### Example Use Case

# CALLING AN AGENT WITH STRUCTURED OUTPUT : 

This issue was surfaced when I was attempting to call an agent passing in a structured output schema and getting back some markdown inside some of the return fields. I've naively attempted to give a custom instruction within the structured output field to ask to remove the markdown which didn't have any effect on the output. Having a discriminated union and/or code comments surfacing the fact that instructions are only used when providing the model field would have provided a better user experience.

