FYI if anyone really needs to workaround this until this bug gets closed, here's how Claude fixed it for us:

Workaround: Replace MCP tool inputSchema after discovery

The issue is that MCPClient.listTools() wraps each tool's inputSchema in a JsonSchemaWrapper that uses AJV for validation. AJV compiles schemas with new Function(), which Workers blocks. Additionally, the fallback path through json-schema-to-zod → resolveSerializedZodOutput also uses new Function().

The fix: after calling listTools(), replace each tool's inputSchema with an AI SDK jsonSchema() wrapper that provides the raw JSON Schema directly and skips AJV validation entirely. The MCP server validates inputs on its end.


import { jsonSchema } from "@mastra/schema-compat";

// After MCPClient.listTools()
const tools = await mcpClient.listTools();

for (const tool of Object.values(tools)) {
  if (tool.inputSchema && typeof tool.inputSchema === "object") {
    // Extract raw JSON Schema from Mastra's JsonSchemaWrapper
    let rawSchema: Record<string, unknown>;
    if (typeof tool.inputSchema.getSchema === "function") {
      // JsonSchemaWrapper stores schema privately; getSchema() exposes it
      rawSchema = tool.inputSchema.getSchema();
    } else if (tool.inputSchema["~standard"]?.jsonSchema?.input) {
      // Fallback: use Standard Schema accessor
      rawSchema = tool.inputSchema["~standard"].jsonSchema.input({
        target: "draft-07",
      });
    } else {
      rawSchema = tool.inputSchema;
    }

    // Re-wrap with passthrough validation (no AJV, no new Function)
    tool.inputSchema = jsonSchema(rawSchema, {
      validate: (value) => ({ success: true, value }),
    });
  }
}
This works because:

jsonSchema() creates a Standard Schema wrapper that passes isStandardSchemaWithJSON, so makeCoreTool takes the direct JSON Schema path — no json-schema-to-zod string eval
The passthrough validate function bypasses AJV compilation entirely
The raw JSON Schema (with type: "object") is preserved for the LLM API call
Tested with @mastra/mcp@1.3.1, @mastra/core@1.14.0, Linear MCP server, on Cloudflare Workers.

