### Describe the Improvement Needed

I think I found a solution for duplicating messages that has multiple issues open (#11397 , #11235 , #11091 , #9370). My use case is client side tool invocations that are automatically  sent with the AI SDK useChat, the issue I encountered is a mismatch between the server generated message ids and the client ones sent back to the server and saved to the db. 

## Current Flow (based on chatRoute code)
 | Step | Action                                                           | Message ID    | Issue                                                                           |
  |------|------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | 1    | User sends message requesting a change that triggers client tool | 1        | -                                                                               |
  | 2    | Agent runs, saves to DB, streams tool call                       | 2  | ❌ No messageId in start event (because lastMessage.role === "user")            |
  | 3    | Client executes tool, sends result back                          |  3      | ❌ Client generated new ID (AI SDK default behavior when no messageId received) |
  | 4    | Agent runs continuation, saves to DB                             | 3 | messageId sent in start (because lastMessage.role === "assistant")              |


## Updated Flow
  | Step | Action                                                           | Message ID | Result                                                                |
  |------|------------------------------------------------------------------|------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | 1    | User sends message requesting a change that triggers client tool | 1          | -                                                                     |
  | 2    | Agent runs, saves to DB, streams tool call                       | 2          | ✅ messageId: 2 sent in start event (using stream.messageId)          |
  | 3    | Client executes tool, sends result back                          | 2          | ✅ Client uses same ID (received from start event)                    |
  | 4    | Agent runs continuation, appends to existing DB message          | 2          | ✅ messageId: 2 sent in start (using lastMessage.id for continuation) |

## Fix
```
  // Only send the last message - memory handles conversation history
  const lastMessage = messages[messages.length - 1];

  // Check if we're continuing an existing assistant message (tool result flow)
  // or starting a new response (user message)
  const isAssistantContinuation = lastMessage?.role === "assistant";

  const stream = await agent.stream(lastMessage, {
    requestContext,
    tracingOptions: {
      metadata: { sessionId: resumeId, userId: "user" },
    },
    memory: {
      thread: resumeId,
      resource: "user",
    },
  });

  // Get the message ID - use Mastra's generated ID for new responses,
  // or continue with the existing ID for assistant continuation
  const serverMessageId = isAssistantContinuation
    ? lastMessage.id
    : stream.messageId;

  // Transform stream into AI SDK format and create UI messages stream
  const uiMessageStream = createUIMessageStream({
    originalMessages: messages,
    execute: async ({ writer }) => {
      // Write start event with our message ID (toAISdkStream would use Mastra's new ID instead)
      writer.write({
        type: "start",
        messageId: serverMessageId,
      });

      for await (const part of toAISdkStream(stream, {
        from: "agent",
        sendStart: false, // We already sent start with correct messageId
        sendFinish: true,
        sendReasoning: true,
        sendSources: true,
      })!) {
        writer.write(part);
      }
    },
  });

  // Create a Response that streams the UI message stream to the client
  return createUIMessageStreamResponse({
    stream: uiMessageStream,
  });
```

