### Problem Statement

We are interested in migrating some of our existing Inngest workflows to Mastra workflows, but we use [Inngest's match/if parameters](https://www.inngest.com/docs/reference/functions/step-wait-for-event) on waitForEvent:

```
// Wait 7 days for an approval and match invoice IDs
const approval = await step.waitForEvent("wait-for-approval", {
  event: "app/invoice.approved",
  timeout: "7d",
  match: "data.invoiceId",
});

// Wait 30 days for a user to start a subscription
// on the pro plan
const subscription = await step.waitForEvent("wait-for-subscription", {
  event: "app/subscription.created",
  timeout: "30d",
  if: "event.data.userId == async.data.userId && async.data.billing_plan == 'pro'",
});
```


### Proposed Solution

API compatible with Inngest's match/if parameters for [wait/if](https://www.inngest.com/docs/reference/functions/step-wait-for-event).

### Component

Workflows

### Alternatives Considered

- Forking Mastra
- implementing the check as code as the first step of the workflow, and bailing/aborting/canceing if it fails

### Example Use Case

As a developer, I want to migrate our user journey workflow to Mastra. This workflow has several match/if conditions on waitForEvent.

